---
title: Lobster Ravioli Gratin with Baby Broccoli and Parmesan Garlic Bread
description: This pasta feast is perfect for a Sunday dinner (although it would be nice, too, for making any night of the week into a celebration). Its centerpiece is ravioli—stuffed with lobster, the king of all shellfish—that get baked with three kinds of cheese and a crispy breadcrumb crust. In other words, it’s creamy, rich, and truly feels and tastes special. And it only gets more exciting when you consider the sides—lemony roasted baby broccoli and cheesy garlic bread toasts.
